  "text": "The magnitude of ARF applied to beads in clotting blood plasma was estimated by measuring displacements in citrated PRP and correlating motion to force using Stokes' law (Eq 1). Bead motion in citrate anticoagulated PRP was compared to that in viscous standards. Terminal bead velocities during ARF application were measured (Fig 3a) and Stokes' law for drag force was used to calculate the force applied to the beads (Fig 3b) [CITATION_1] . Stokes' law is:",
